<inglise> Commission Regulation (EC) No 2051/97 of 20 October 1997 establishing detailed rules for the implementation of the provisions relating to the allocation of a 'plant- health control' financial contribution from the Community </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2051/97, milles s&auml;testatakse &uuml;henduse poolt f&uuml;tosanitaarkontrolliks ette n&auml;htud rahaliste toetuste jaotamist k&auml;sitlevate s&auml;tete &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad 20. oktoober 1997 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Directive 77/93/EEC of 21 December 1976 on protective measures against the introduction into the Community of organisms harmful to plants or plant products and against their spread within the Community (1), as last amended by Commission Directive 97/14/EC (2), and in particular the last subparagraph of Article 19c (5) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 21. detsembri 1976. aasta direktiivi 77/93/EM&Uuml; taimi v&otilde;i taimseid saadusi kahjustavate organismide &uuml;hendusse toomist ja nende levikut &uuml;henduses takistavate kaitsemeetmete kohta, (1) viimati muudetud komisjoni direktiiviga 97/14/E&Uuml;, (2) eriti selle artikli 19c viimast l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, pursuant to the provisions of Directive 77/93/EEC, a 'plant-health control' financial contribution from the Community may be granted to Member States to cover expenditure relating directly to the necessary specific measures which have been taken or are planned for the purpose of combating the harmful organisms introduced from third countries or from other areas in the Community, in order to eradicate or, if that is not possible, contain them; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: vastavalt direktiivi 77/93/EM&Uuml; s&auml;tetele v&otilde;ib liikmesriikidele anda f&uuml;tosanitaarkontrolliks etten&auml;htud rahalist toetust, et katta v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i v&otilde;etavate vajalike erimeetmetega otseselt seotud kulutusi ning v&otilde;idelda kahjulike organismide kolmandatest riikidest v&otilde;i teistelt &uuml;henduse aladelt sissetoomise vastu v&otilde;i, kui see ei ole v&otilde;imalik, need likvideerida; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, moreover, Member States may, in particular, request to receive a Community financial contribution for their specific measures which they have adopted or planned to adopt to control infections by harmful organisms introduced in their territory; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriigid v&otilde;ivad samuti eelk&otilde;ige taotleda &uuml;henduse rahalist toetust v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i v&otilde;etavate erimeetmete jaoks, et t&otilde;kestada oma territooriumile toodud kahjulike organismide p&otilde;hjustatud nakkuste levikut; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is necessary to provide for detailed rules for the implementation of the provisions relating to the allocation of a 'plant-health control' financial contribution from the Community; </inglise>
<eesti> on vaja s&auml;testada &uuml;henduse poolt f&uuml;tosanitaarkontrolliks etten&auml;htud rahaliste toetuste jaotamist k&auml;sitlevate s&auml;tete &uuml;ksikasjalikud rakenduseeskirjad; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas these rules should be met by Member States when entering an application to qualify for the said Community financial contribution; </inglise>
<eesti> liikmesriigid peaksid nimetatud &uuml;henduse rahalise toetuse taotlemisel neid eeskirju t&auml;itma; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Standing Committee on Plant Health, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las alalise taimetervise komitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The application of Member States for the allocation of a 'plant-health control' financial contribution from the Community pursuant to Article 19c (5) of Directive 77/93/EEC, shall be: </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigi taotluse &uuml;henduse rahalise toetuse saamiseks f&uuml;tosanitaarkontrolli jaoks vastavalt direktiivi 77/93/EM&Uuml; artikli 19c l&otilde;ikele 5 peab: </eesti>
<inglise> - entered in a written form by the single central authority referred to in Article 1 (6) of Directive 77/93/EEC, and </inglise>
<eesti> - esitama kirjalikult direktiivi 77/93/EM&Uuml; artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 6 osutatud &uuml;htne keskasutus, ja </eesti>
<inglise> - addressed to the Commission of the European Communities, Director General of DG VI, Rue de la Loi/Wetstraat 200, B-1049 Brussels, and </inglise>
<eesti> - adresseerima Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Komisjonile, VI peadirektoraadi peadirektorile, Rue de la Loi/Wetstraat 200, B-1049 Br&uuml;ssel, ja </eesti>
<inglise> - submitted by 15 October 1997, if to be taken into account for the appropriations for that purpose in the general budget of the European Union for the financial year 1997, and by 1 July of each subsequent year, if to be taken into account for the appropriations for that purpose in the general budget of the European Union for that year. </inglise>
<eesti> - esitama 15. oktoobriks 1997, kui soovitakse, et see v&otilde;etakse sel eesm&auml;rgil arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse 1997. majandusaasta &uuml;ldeelarve assigneeringutes, ja iga j&auml;rgneva aasta 1. juuliks, kui soovitakse, et see v&otilde;etakse sel eesm&auml;rgil arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse selle aasta assigneeringutes. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 20 October 1997. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 20. oktoober 1997 </eesti>
